reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2012
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Yummy baby food!
reviews.reviewText: I was advised by my pediatrician to start feeding my baby cereal to get him accustomed to the taste and texture of food. Hubby and I excitedly went out and got for him "G___" rice cereal. My poor baby was making faces while eating his rice cereal but was a pretty good sport and still swallowed. I was fed Cerelac as a baby and I decided that my baby should try some too. He was smiling and laughing while I was feeding him Cerelac. He obviously enjoyed his dinner. :-) My only concern is that the 4 pack cans expire on 10/12 and I don't know if my baby will be able to eat everything by then, since he's also taking breast milk. I wish the cans will have a later expiration date. Next time, I will just stick to the single cans. Although pricier, I will be sure there won't be any waste.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2011
reviews.reviewText: My daughter never liked Gerber or Beech Nut cereals and was always spitting up after eating. It was a tough job to feed her and we tried every type of cereal that's available locally.On a vacation trip last year, we bought this cereal and she loved it. After returning home, we tried to find it but could not find a store that carried it. As a last resort, I searched for it on Amazon and to a big relief Amazon had it. It's a little pricey on Amazon but at least my daughter eats it without any problem. We have been mixing it with milk instead of water and she seems to like that. Great product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2012
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent, product, fast delivery
reviews.reviewText: My husband and I have been ordering cerelac for a year now. We transitioned from the wheat and milk to the wheat, milk and honey after our daughter turned one. This breakfast cereal has been a God send for us as working parents, it is easy to fix, its clearly our babies favorite food and it is nutritious without all the sodium/sugars you may find in regular cereal. I highly recommend this product. Nestle Cerelac, Honey and Wheat with Milk, 14.11-Ounce Cans (Pack of 4)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2012
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than the rest intro to solid food 101
reviews.reviewText: I wish I could give a 10 star rating... But that aside, although the taste is not as great as it used to be when I was an infant, my baby still loves it all the same, and I recommend it to the daycare teachers at my child's school for future reference for babies experiencing the same predicament as mine-- i.e. babies who just can't taste/eat the puree food in the bottles and plastics and won't drink milk of any kind from a feeding bottle-- This was a life saver for me. AMAZON, thanks for the package but I want to suggest PACKAGE of 10 instead of 4, for someone like me who loves to buy in bulk. Thx.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good solid product to keep handy.
reviews.reviewText: Thankfully, Cerelac hasn't changed since I was a kid. The taste takes me back, and the kids do eat it up. Nothing like fresh fruits and veggies, but very good to keep handy for that rainy day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Toddler loves this superb cereal, expensive though..
reviews.reviewText: My 2 Year old Toddler's most liked food is his cereal. The taste is so delectable, toddler can hardly resist it. Packaging and shipment is great. One of the finest food texture for babies to eat/chew. I has good nutrition value as well. he only factor I disliked, is it's too expensive (34$ for 4, 8.5$ per 14.11 ounce can. I searched it in retail offline giant store but couldn't find any. It lasts only 1 month for us, so we need it each month, so I was expecting a price bracket around 25 max.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 7, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good product, to expensive
reviews.reviewText: Move it, bit I still don't understand why here 1.6 kg (4 cans) cost above $30 while in Europe 2 kg cost $7 to $8. If the price was lower you would sell a lot. Right now we control how much we can give to our kid and only offer him on special occasions and not daily as we would like. The product itself is very good although I prefer the Portuguese version - it requires a lot less powder to have the same amount of prepared cerelac
I think the shipping is way too expensive but good product

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on June 11, 2015
reviews.reviewText: I ate it as a child and so did my wife, hence it was an obvious choice for us to offer to our daughter from start of her weaning. Not only did she took to it as fish to water, this has made easy for us to mix fruit and veges in puree form and offer her as meals during the day time. This is one constant snack/breakfast/meal that she enjoyed from 6 to 14 months. Absolutely recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 28, 2011
reviews.reviewText: Our baby really loves Cerelac. Great product for his development. It's great to find it at this price on Amazon because we can't find it in store now. Quick delivery and good packaging.
Very yummy cereal but price went up too much from 2017 40$ to 2020 to 125$ way to expensive
